the API must return a single, valid JSON object with exactly these fields no more not less:
● id → string (UUID)
● title → string
● body → string (original article text)
● summary → string
● tags → array of strings
● relevance_score → number (0.0–1.0)
● source_url → string
● publisher → string
● published_at → string (ISO 8601)
● ingested_at → string (ISO 8601)
● media → object containing:
● featured_image_url → string (real, working image URL)
● related_video_url → string (real, working video URL)
● media_justification → string (Qwen-generated rationale)
● context → object containing:
● wikipedia_snippet → string
● social_sentiment → string
● search_trend → string
● geo → object with:
● lat → number
● lng → number
● map_url → string
